title._content: Fire on Roxbury Street, Keene NH, July 4, 1905

description._content: TITLE Fire on Roxbury Street, Keene NH, July 4, 1905 CREATOR SUBJECT Fires - NH - Keene DESCRIPTION Photograph of a fire on Roxbury Street, Keene New Hampshire, on July 4, 1905. "At 1:40 p.m. Box 9 was rung for a fire in the restaurant of F.O. Quinn, in the building which formerly occupied the site of the State liquor store. The restaurant was established by the late P.J. O'Brien, and the building, with the adjoining one still standing, were moved to Roxbury street from the vicinity of the former Hayward house on Court Street."
